Czech Stocks Decline, Extend Biggest Weekly Retreat Since April

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-07-15T14:59:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/czech-stocks-decline-second-day-head-for-worst-week-since-april.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark stock
index fell for a second day, extending its biggest weekly drop
in three months, as  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the country’s biggest power utility,
and coal company New World Resources Plc declined.  The PX gauge, where CEZ has a 19 percent weighting, dropped
0.2 percent to 1,199.2 at its 4:28 p.m. close in Prague. It lost
1.7 percent this week, the most since the five days ended April
15. CEZ and NWR both retreated more than 1.4 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  